				<h4 id="syntax">
					Syntax
				</h4>
				<p>
					The syntax for <mono>replace_vars</mono> calls is:
<div align="center" style="margin-top:-15px; margin-bottom:25px">
<mono>f++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline lang-nift" style="margin-bottom:-27px">
replace_vars()
replace_vars(bool) 
</pre>
</div><br>
<div align="center" style="margin-top:-15px; margin-bottom:15px">
<mono>n++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline lang-nift" style="margin-bottom:-27px">
\@replace_vars()
\@replace_vars(bool) 
</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="description">
					Description
				</h4>
				<p>
					The <mono>replace_vars</mono> function is for getting and setting whether to replace variables with values where applicable by default, for example with <mono>console</mono>, <mono>&&</mono> and <mono>||</mono> calls. It either:
					<ul>
						<li>takes zero parameters and returns whether variables are replaced with values where applicable by default; or</li>
						<li>takes a single boolean parameter specifying whether to replace variables with values where applicable by default (default value is <mono>1</mono>).</li>
					</ul>
				</p>

				<h4 id="f++-eg">
					f++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>replace_vars</mono> being used with <mono>f++</mono>:					

<div align="center">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums lang-nift">
replace_vars(0)
console(replace_vars())</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="n++-eg">
					n++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>replace_vars</mono> being used with <mono>n++</mono>:					

<div align="center">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums lang-nift">
\@replace_vars(0)
\@console(replace_vars())</pre>
</div>
				</p>
			</div>
